section.div: Random QoL stuff for Spicetify users/devs
Easily make Spicetify extensions and custom apps.

div.div:
feat(testing): implement unit tests for core services and visualizers
Introduces Vitest for unit testing and sets up the necessary configuration and mocking infrastructure.
- Adds comprehensive tests for the `SettingsService`, verifying default value handling, loading from local storage, and saving new settings. - Implements tests for the `BarSpectrumVisualizer`, ensuring correct rendering logic based on audio data and user settings like `mirror`. - Refactors `AudioService` and `BarSpectrumVisualizer` to align with the base visualizer contract and improve testability. - Corrects the `draw` method signature in `BaseVisualizer` to enforce a consistent contract for all visualizers.

feat(core): implement foundational architecture and bar spectrum
Implements the core architectural components of the spicetify-viz application, establishing the foundational patterns for all future development.
- Creates the singleton services for audio analysis (`core/audio.ts`), dynamic theming (`core/theme.ts`), and settings management (`core/settings.ts`). - Defines the base visualizer contract (`visualizers/base.ts`) and the visualizer registry. - Implements the first concrete visualizer, `Bar Spectrum`, with full support for its documented settings. - Overhauls `app.tsx` to act as the central orchestrator, managing state with signals, running the render loop, and handling the visualizer lifecycle. - Adds a dynamic settings UI that is generated automatically from the Zod settings schema.

Initial commit with project setup, including .gitignore, package.json, pnpm-lock.yaml, workspace configuration, and various documentation files. Added components and utilities for the spicetify-viz project, along with initial styling and layout configurations.

Add Vercel serverless function for SSR and update routing configuration
This commit introduces a new serverless function in `api/ssr.ts` to handle server-side rendering (SSR) requests, based on the official Vike + Vercel example. The previous API entry point in `index.ts` has been removed, and the Vercel configuration in `vercel.json` has been updated to route requests appropriately, ensuring compatibility with the new SSR setup. Additionally, the `@vercel/node` dependency has been added to support the serverless function integration.

Update API entry point to support serverless function integration
This commit modifies the API entry point in `index.ts` to serve as a serverless function that imports the Vike server entry. The change enhances compatibility with Vercel's serverless environment by exporting all necessary components from the server entry, ensuring proper functionality in the deployment setup.
